This document explains the most useful and professional Visual Studio Code extensions for Python,
why they are important, and how they improve your daily workflow.
These extensions are widely used by students, engineers, data scientists, and professional developers.

ğŸ Python (by Microsoft)
Publisher: Microsoft
Extension ID: ms-python.python
This is the core and mandatory extension for Python in VS Code.

---

Why it is important

-Enables Python support in VS Code
-Connects VS Code with your Python interpreter
-Works seamlessly with .venv

---

Main features

-Python code execution
-Interpreter selection
-Debugging tools
-IntelliSense (basic auto-completion)
-Linting support

âœ… Without this extension, VS Code cannot work properly with Python.

---

ğŸ§  Pylance

Publisher: Microsoft
Extension ID: ms-python.vscode-pylance

Pylance is a high-performance language server for Python.

---

Why it is important

-Makes VS Code "understand" your Python code
-Detects errors before running the program
-Main features
-Advanced auto-completion
-Type checking
-Faster IntelliSense
-Error detection in real time

âœ… Strongly recommended for professional-quality code.

---

ğŸ¨ Python Indent

Publisher: Kevin Rose
